10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Department of
Commerce; appropriating certain funds in certain
12 amount for certain purpose; directing utilization of
certain amounts for certain purposes; providing for
13 noncodification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
20 Commerce from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the General
21 Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year ending June
22 30, 2027, the sum of Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($500,000.00) or
23 so much thereof as may be necessary to perform the duties imposed
24 upon the Oklahoma Department of Commerce by law.
Req. No. 17403 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
2 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
3 Funds appropriated by Section 1 of this act shall be utilized as
4 follows:
5 Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($500,000.00) to be transferred to
6 the U.S. Decennial Census Revolving Fund created by Enrolled House
7 Bill No. 3622 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
8 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
9 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
10 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
11 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
12 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
